# API changes include UI

When adding or extending backend API endpoints, also implement the corresponding web UI in the same change unless the user explicitly scopes the work to API-only.

Minimum UI deliverable per feature:

- Dashboard route(s) under `apps/web/app/dashboard/` (or `platform/` for super-admin APIs)
- TanStack Query reads/writes via `useApiQuery` / `useApiMutation`
- EN + MY strings in `messages/en.json` and `messages/my.json`
- Nav link when the feature is a top-level area
- Loading, empty, and error states
- Seed or demo data when the feature needs setup to be exercised locally

Do not leave read-only API endpoints with no way to verify them in the browser.
